1 A RESOLUTION recognizing and commending Bowman Skunk Works for
2 empowering Kentucky students for a future in the aviation industry.
3 WHEREAS, Bowman Skunk Works is a unique nonprofit organization that offers
4 adult mentors to high school students in the area of aerospace education, including the
5 building of Van's RV-12 Light Sport aircrafts, for an amazing experience of learning,
6 teamwork, growth, and accomplishment; and
7 WHEREAS, Bowman Skunk Works is located on the south side of Bowman Field,
8 a public airport in Louisville, Kentucky, where students have the opportunity for flight
9 training experiences and to become a part of the wonderful and vibrant aviation
10 community at Bowman Field; and
11 WHEREAS, students in the program have the opportunity to work alongside United
12 Parcel Service aircraft engineering, flight operation, and aircraft maintenance retirees.
13 They are also provided experiences such as riding in a Van's RV-12, touring local
14 aviation facilities, and other exciting activities centered around aviation and engineering;
15 and
16 WHEREAS, during their building experience, students can work towards their
17 private pilot certificate; and
18 WHEREAS, Bowman Skunk Works students recently engaged with the University
19 of Louisville J.B. Speed School of Engineering in their capstone senior project to convert
20 a Van's RV-12 to an all-electric aircraft; and
21 WHEREAS, recognizing that battery and electric motor technology are making new
22 breakthroughs regularly, which will reduce weight, extend flying range, simplify
23 maintenance and operation, and improve costs, Bowman Skunk Works provides early
24 and invaluable exposure to young people interested in learning about the industry;
25 NOW, THEREFORE,
26 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
27 Kentucky:
